<div class="content_well top">
	<div class="the_hub_content_wrapper the_hub_article">
		<div class="the_hub_content">
		<a href="/category/the-hub/" class="header_link">
		<div class="the_hub_title_wrapper">
			<div class="the_hub_logo">
				<img src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/plugins/lb-content-widgets/img/lit-horn.svg">
			</div>
			<div class="the_hub_title">
				<h1>The Hub</h1>
			</div>
			<div class="the_hub_slogan">
				<h1>News, Notes, Talk</h1>
			</div>
		</div>
		</a>
		
				<div class="the_hub_item">
			<div class="banner_img">
				<a href="https://lithub.com/what-to-read-next-based-on-your-favorite-tony-nominee/" title="What to read next based on your favorite Tony nominee.">
		    		<img src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/4eebb7e0bddb56b5ee0a73d2706385e8-playbill-cover-cluster-02-hr-1240x828.jpg" alt="" class="post_ft entry_post"/>
		    	</a>
			</div>
			
			<div class="post_content">
				<h1 data-report-url="/what-to-read-next-based-on-your-favorite-tony-nominee/"><a href="https://lithub.com/what-to-read-next-based-on-your-favorite-tony-nominee/">What to read next based on your favorite Tony nominee.</a></h1>
				
				<div class="author_info">
					<div class="author_photo"><img src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/ESTRed-121-1-scaled-e1711474962955-100x100.jpg" width="100" height="100" alt="Brittany Allen" class="avatar avatar-100 wp-user-avatar wp-user-avatar-100 alignnone photo" /></div>
					<div class="author_name">By&nbsp;<a href="https://lithub.com/author/brittanyallen/" itemprop="url"><span itemprop="name">Brittany&nbsp;Allen</span></a></div>
					<div class="author_hr"><hr/></div>
					<div class="publish_date">June 14, 2024, 1:25pm</div>
				</div>
				
				<p>This Sunday, Broadway will recognize some of the year&#8217;s plays and musicals with <a href="https://www.tonyawards.com/nominees/" class="external" target="_blank">a shiny celebration</a> and a great many inside jokes. Maybe you&#8217;ve seen some of the nominated plays. Or maybe you will, later, when they <a href="https://www.pbs.org/wnet/gperf/collections/broadway-pbs/?utm_source=GPGoogle&amp;utm_medium=cpc&amp;utm_campaign=broadwayandbeyond&amp;gad_source=1&amp;gclid=CjwKCAjw1K-zBhBIEiwAWeCOF21sgCETzwaq0y8DHLXXW5YJmiMe_hI5j7V6yC_GkWlx_-e3dTcAohoCl3sQAvD_BwE" class="external" target="_blank">reach PBS</a> or your town.</p>
<p>Either way, as a Lit Hub reader, you may be interested to know that some of this year&#8217;s biggest tickets are<em> literary adaptations</em>. Which prompted this viewer to wonder, what happens if we reverse-engineer the usual pipeline? And you leave the theatre with a wish to pick up a book? Well, dear reader, I&#8217;ve got that urge covered. Here are some prose recommendations based on some of this season&#8217;s biggest shows, i.e., your Tony bracket.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>WHAT TO READ IF YOU LOVED:</strong></p>
<span class="caption"><img fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="238632" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/what-to-read-next-based-on-your-favorite-tony-nominee/via-today-t/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/via-today-t.jpg" data-orig-size="1079,720" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Kalyne Coleman and Maechi Aharanwa in Jaja&#8217;s African Hair Braiding. (Matthew Murphy)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/via-today-t-300x200.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/via-today-t.jpg" class="wp-image-238632 size-full" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/via-today-t.jpg" alt="" width="1079" height="720" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/via-today-t.jpg 1079w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/via-today-t-300x200.jpg 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/via-today-t-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/via-today-t-60x40.jpg 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/via-today-t-50x33.jpg 50w" sizes="(max-width: 1079px) 100vw, 1079px" /> Kalyne Coleman and Maechi Aharanwa in Jaja&#8217;s African Hair Braiding. (Matthew Murphy)</span>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.manhattantheatreclub.com/shows/2023-24-season/jajas-african-hair-braiding/" class="external" target="_blank"><em><strong>Jaja&#8217;s African Hair Braiding</strong></em></a>, <strong>Jocelyn Bioh</strong></p>
<p><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="238599" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/what-to-read-next-based-on-your-favorite-tony-nominee/91a6a-u9x-s-_ac_uf10001000_ql80_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/91A6a-U9X-S._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" data-orig-size="662,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="91A6a-U9X-S._AC_UF1000,1000_QL80_" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/91A6a-U9X-S._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-199x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/91A6a-U9X-S._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" class="size-medium wp-image-238599 aligncenter" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/91A6a-U9X-S._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-199x300.jpg" alt="" width="199" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/91A6a-U9X-S._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-199x300.jpg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/91A6a-U9X-S._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/91A6a-U9X-S._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/91A6a-U9X-S._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg 662w" sizes="(max-width: 199px) 100vw, 199px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Kaitlyn Greenidge, <a href="https://bookshop.org/p/books/libertie-kaitlyn-greenidge/15861166?ean=9781643752587" class="external" target="_blank"><em>Libertie</em></a></strong></p>
<p>Like <em>Jaja</em>, this beautifully structured novel depicts a totalizing mother/daughter relationship in which Mom is a charisma magnet who assumes her daughter will follow in her professional footsteps.</p>
<p>And for another fictional exploration of mothering in community, you might revisit Brit Bennett&#8217;s stellar debut, <a href="https://bookshop.org/p/books/the-mothers-brit-bennett/10206851?ean=9780399184529" class="external" target="_blank"><em>The Mothers.</em></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>WHAT TO READ IF YOU LOVED:</strong></p>
<span class="caption"><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="238634" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/what-to-read-next-based-on-your-favorite-tony-nominee/april-and-rachel/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/april-and-rachel.jpg" data-orig-size="1200,600" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="april and rachel" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/april-and-rachel-300x150.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/april-and-rachel.jpg" class="wp-image-238634 size-full" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/april-and-rachel.jpg" alt="" width="1200" height="600" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/april-and-rachel.jpg 1200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/april-and-rachel-300x150.jpg 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/april-and-rachel-768x384.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/april-and-rachel-60x30.jpg 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/april-and-rachel-50x25.jpg 50w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /> April Matthis and Rachel McAdams in Mary Jane. (Matthew Murphy)</span>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong><a href="https://www.manhattantheatreclub.com/shows/2023-24-season/mary-jane/?utm_source=google&amp;utm_medium=cpc&amp;gad_source=1&amp;gclid=CjwKCAjw1K-zBhBIEiwAWeCOF6pOhWWjlGV5yIPnzf_HOQe4a4g8Daj17ii1VXOTnNeuv0Tpl7Y-iRoCjbcQAvD_BwE" class="external" target="_blank"><em>Mary Jane</em></a>, Amy Herzog</strong></p>
<p>One of this year&#8217;s frontrunners for Best Play is this quiet, powerful meditation on the logistics of caregiving. If you&#8217;re likewise compelled by the agony and banality of chronic crises, or the village it can take to manage an emergency, you might appreciate these.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="238597" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/what-to-read-next-based-on-your-favorite-tony-nominee/51rysle2tol-_ac_uf10001000_ql80_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/51rYSLE2ToL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" data-orig-size="688,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="51rYSLE2ToL._AC_UF1000,1000_QL80_" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/51rYSLE2ToL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-206x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/51rYSLE2ToL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" class="size-medium wp-image-238597 aligncenter" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/51rYSLE2ToL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-206x300.jpg" alt="" width="206" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/51rYSLE2ToL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-206x300.jpg 206w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/51rYSLE2ToL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-41x60.jpg 41w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/51rYSLE2ToL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-34x50.jpg 34w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/51rYSLE2ToL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg 688w" sizes="(max-width: 206px) 100vw, 206px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Miriam Toews, <a href="https://bookshop.org/p/books/all-my-puny-sorrows-miriam-toews/8556828?ean=9781635574975" class="external" target="_blank"><em>All My Puny Sorrows</em></a></strong></p>
<p>This is one of my constant recommendations. I love this witty, heartbreakingly frank story about two sisters who can&#8217;t save each other. Like MJ, this is a book that models how we bear unbearable things. It is stupid good. Please pick it up, if you&#8217;ve been hiding away from it, under a rock.</p>
<p>While I&#8217;m in the neighborhood? Patricia Lockwood&#8217;s <a href="https://bookshop.org/p/books/no-one-is-talking-about-this-patricia-lockwood/14728058?ean=9780593189597" class="external" target="_blank"><em>No One is Talking About This</em></a> is also sage on caregiving. A lot of the criticism of that much-feted debut novel dwelled on its internettiness. But its heart-cracking second half is a bona fide meditation in an emergency.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>WHAT TO READ IF YOU LOVED:</strong></p>
<span class="caption"><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="238635" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/what-to-read-next-based-on-your-favorite-tony-nominee/celia-keenan-bolger-and-jessica-lange-in-mother-play/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Celia-Keenan-Bolger-and-Jessica-Lange-in-Mother-Play.jpg" data-orig-size="970,546" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Celia-Keenan-Bolger-and-Jessica-Lange-in-Mother-Play" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Jessica Lange and Celia Keenan-Bolger. Photo by Joan Marcus.&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Celia-Keenan-Bolger-and-Jessica-Lange-in-Mother-Play-300x169.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Celia-Keenan-Bolger-and-Jessica-Lange-in-Mother-Play.jpg" class="wp-image-238635 size-full" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Celia-Keenan-Bolger-and-Jessica-Lange-in-Mother-Play.jpg" alt="" width="970" height="546" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Celia-Keenan-Bolger-and-Jessica-Lange-in-Mother-Play.jpg 970w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Celia-Keenan-Bolger-and-Jessica-Lange-in-Mother-Play-300x169.jpg 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Celia-Keenan-Bolger-and-Jessica-Lange-in-Mother-Play-768x432.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Celia-Keenan-Bolger-and-Jessica-Lange-in-Mother-Play-60x34.jpg 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Celia-Keenan-Bolger-and-Jessica-Lange-in-Mother-Play-50x28.jpg 50w" sizes="(max-width: 970px) 100vw, 970px" /> Jessica Lange and Celia Keenan-Bolger in Mother Play. (Joan Marcus)</span>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://2st.com/shows/mother-play" class="external" target="_blank"><em><strong>Mother Play</strong></em></a>, <strong>Paula Vogel</strong></p>
<p>The great Paula Vogel is <em>also</em> dancing with motherhood this season, in her aptly titled <em>Mother Play. </em>I have two books for fans of this one.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="238538" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/what-to-read-next-based-on-your-favorite-tony-nominee/36101014-1/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/36101014-1.jpg" data-orig-size="1400,2100" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="36101014-1" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/36101014-1-200x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/36101014-1-683x1024.jpg" class="size-medium wp-image-238538 aligncenter" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/36101014-1-200x300.jpg" alt="" width="200" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/36101014-1-200x300.jpg 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/36101014-1-683x1024.jpg 683w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/36101014-1-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/36101014-1-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/36101014-1-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/36101014-1-1365x2048.jpg 1365w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/36101014-1-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/36101014-1.jpg 1400w" sizes="(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Samuel Park, <a href="https://bookshop.org/p/books/the-caregiver-samuel-park/6684221?ean=9781501178795" class="external" target="_blank"><em>The Caregiver</em></a></strong></p>
<p>In this lushly told story, the late Samuel Park examines, yes, <em>another</em> vexed mother/daughter relationship. But this one is a moving emotional thrill ride concerning the secrets we keep from our loved ones.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="238536" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/what-to-read-next-based-on-your-favorite-tony-nominee/91gdehsxq7l-_ac_uf10001000_ql80_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/91GdEhsxQ7L._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" data-orig-size="647,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="91GdEhsxQ7L._AC_UF1000,1000_QL80_" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/91GdEhsxQ7L._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-194x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/91GdEhsxQ7L._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" class="aligncenter wp-image-238536 size-medium" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/91GdEhsxQ7L._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-194x300.jpg" alt="" width="194" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/91GdEhsxQ7L._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-194x300.jpg 194w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/91GdEhsxQ7L._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/91GdEhsxQ7L._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-32x50.jpg 32w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/91GdEhsxQ7L._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg 647w" sizes="(max-width: 194px) 100vw, 194px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Gwendoline Riley, <a href="https://bookshop.org/p/books/my-phantoms-gwendoline-riley/17788884?ean=9781681376813" class="external" target="_blank"><em>My Phantoms</em></a></strong></p>
<p>For another angle on maddening matriarchs and the psychic ties they bind, look no further than this itchy-making portrait. Riley&#8217;s mother might be less glamorously charming than Rachel McAdams or Jessica Lange, but she&#8217;s no less plausible. Or mysterious to her children.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>WHAT TO READ IF YOU LOVED:</strong></p>
<span class="caption"><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="238636" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/what-to-read-next-based-on-your-favorite-tony-nominee/sarah-paulson-and-elle-fanning-in-appropriate/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Sarah-Paulson-and-Elle-Fanning-in-Appropriate.jpg" data-orig-size="970,546" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Sarah-Paulson-and-Elle-Fanning-in-Appropriate" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Sarah Paulson and Elle Fanning in Appropriate. (Joan Marcus)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Sarah-Paulson-and-Elle-Fanning-in-Appropriate-300x169.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Sarah-Paulson-and-Elle-Fanning-in-Appropriate.jpg" class="wp-image-238636 size-full" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Sarah-Paulson-and-Elle-Fanning-in-Appropriate.jpg" alt="" width="970" height="546" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Sarah-Paulson-and-Elle-Fanning-in-Appropriate.jpg 970w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Sarah-Paulson-and-Elle-Fanning-in-Appropriate-300x169.jpg 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Sarah-Paulson-and-Elle-Fanning-in-Appropriate-768x432.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Sarah-Paulson-and-Elle-Fanning-in-Appropriate-60x34.jpg 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Sarah-Paulson-and-Elle-Fanning-in-Appropriate-50x28.jpg 50w" sizes="(max-width: 970px) 100vw, 970px" /> Sarah Paulson and Elle Fanning in Appropriate. (Joan Marcus)</span>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em><strong><a href="https://appropriateplay.com/?gad_source=1&amp;gclid=CjwKCAjw1K-zBhBIEiwAWeCOF0TcMzFqGWkiaRd11CrmAMDCaQnPVZkozBizsI8aw3KFNWluCIID-RoCpJ4QAvD_BwE" class="external" target="_blank">Appropriate</a>,</strong></em><strong> Branden Jacobs-Jenkins</strong></p>
<p>In this thorny drama, a white family returns to their Arkansas homestead only to find ghosts in the attic. This script is a <a href="https://bookshop.org/p/books/appropriate-an-octoroon-plays-branden-jacobs-jenkins/10492269?ean=9781559364904" class="external" target="_blank">great read</a> in itself.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="238602" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/what-to-read-next-based-on-your-favorite-tony-nominee/81aed7wpr9l-_ac_uf10001000_ql80_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/81aeD7wPR9L._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" data-orig-size="662,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="81aeD7wPR9L._AC_UF1000,1000_QL80_" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/81aeD7wPR9L._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-199x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/81aeD7wPR9L._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" class="size-medium wp-image-238602 aligncenter" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/81aeD7wPR9L._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-199x300.jpg" alt="" width="199" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/81aeD7wPR9L._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-199x300.jpg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/81aeD7wPR9L._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/81aeD7wPR9L._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/81aeD7wPR9L._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg 662w" sizes="(max-width: 199px) 100vw, 199px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Mat Johnson, <a href="https://bookshop.org/p/books/loving-day-mat-johnson/16622522?ean=9780812983661" class="external" target="_blank"><em>Loving Day</em></a> </strong></p>
<p>But if you&#8217;re looking for fiction that troubles similar waters (re: the spiritual gymnastics some of us do to ignore race and racial violence, the fraught attics of American homes), I&#8217;d look to this smart, wicked offering from Mat Johnson.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="238608" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/what-to-read-next-based-on-your-favorite-tony-nominee/9780449911877-us/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/9780449911877-us.jpg" data-orig-size="311,475" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="9780449911877-us" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/9780449911877-us-196x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/9780449911877-us.jpg" class="size-medium wp-image-238608 aligncenter" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/9780449911877-us-196x300.jpg" alt="" width="196" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/9780449911877-us-196x300.jpg 196w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/9780449911877-us-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/9780449911877-us-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/9780449911877-us.jpg 311w" sizes="(max-width: 196px) 100vw, 196px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Allan Gurganus, <a href="https://bookshop.org/p/books/white-people-allan-gurganus/8503407?ean=9780375704277" class="external" target="_blank"><em>White People</em></a></strong></p>
<p><em>Appropriate</em> also inclined me to revisit the stories of Allan Gurganus, that self-appointed bard of the Southern white soul. This voicey, hilarious collection is worth digging into.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>WHAT TO READ IF YOU LOVED:</strong></p>
<span class="caption"><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="238637" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/what-to-read-next-based-on-your-favorite-tony-nominee/10-kara-young-heather-alicia-simms-leslie-odom-jr-vanessa-bell-calloway-billy-eugene-jones-and-noah-robbins-in-purlie-victorious-photo-by-marc-j-franklin/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/10-Kara-Young-Heather-Alicia-Simms-Leslie-Odom-Jr.-Vanessa-Bell-Calloway-Billy-Eugene-Jones-and-Noah-Robbins-in-PURLIE-VICTORIOUS-Photo-by-Marc-J.-Franklin.jpg" data-orig-size="970,546" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="10-Kara-Young-Heather-Alicia-Simms-Leslie-Odom-Jr.-Vanessa-Bell-Calloway-Billy-Eugene-Jones-and-Noah-Robbins-in-PURLIE-VICTORIOUS-Photo-by-Marc-J.-Franklin" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Kara Young, Heather Alicia Simms, Leslie Odom, Jr., Vanessa Bell Calloway, Billy Eugene Jones, and Noah Robbins in Purlie Victorious. (Marc J. Franklin)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/10-Kara-Young-Heather-Alicia-Simms-Leslie-Odom-Jr.-Vanessa-Bell-Calloway-Billy-Eugene-Jones-and-Noah-Robbins-in-PURLIE-VICTORIOUS-Photo-by-Marc-J.-Franklin-300x169.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/10-Kara-Young-Heather-Alicia-Simms-Leslie-Odom-Jr.-Vanessa-Bell-Calloway-Billy-Eugene-Jones-and-Noah-Robbins-in-PURLIE-VICTORIOUS-Photo-by-Marc-J.-Franklin.jpg" class="wp-image-238637 size-full" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/10-Kara-Young-Heather-Alicia-Simms-Leslie-Odom-Jr.-Vanessa-Bell-Calloway-Billy-Eugene-Jones-and-Noah-Robbins-in-PURLIE-VICTORIOUS-Photo-by-Marc-J.-Franklin.jpg" alt="" width="970" height="546" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/10-Kara-Young-Heather-Alicia-Simms-Leslie-Odom-Jr.-Vanessa-Bell-Calloway-Billy-Eugene-Jones-and-Noah-Robbins-in-PURLIE-VICTORIOUS-Photo-by-Marc-J.-Franklin.jpg 970w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/10-Kara-Young-Heather-Alicia-Simms-Leslie-Odom-Jr.-Vanessa-Bell-Calloway-Billy-Eugene-Jones-and-Noah-Robbins-in-PURLIE-VICTORIOUS-Photo-by-Marc-J.-Franklin-300x169.jpg 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/10-Kara-Young-Heather-Alicia-Simms-Leslie-Odom-Jr.-Vanessa-Bell-Calloway-Billy-Eugene-Jones-and-Noah-Robbins-in-PURLIE-VICTORIOUS-Photo-by-Marc-J.-Franklin-768x432.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/10-Kara-Young-Heather-Alicia-Simms-Leslie-Odom-Jr.-Vanessa-Bell-Calloway-Billy-Eugene-Jones-and-Noah-Robbins-in-PURLIE-VICTORIOUS-Photo-by-Marc-J.-Franklin-60x34.jpg 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/10-Kara-Young-Heather-Alicia-Simms-Leslie-Odom-Jr.-Vanessa-Bell-Calloway-Billy-Eugene-Jones-and-Noah-Robbins-in-PURLIE-VICTORIOUS-Photo-by-Marc-J.-Franklin-50x28.jpg 50w" sizes="(max-width: 970px) 100vw, 970px" /> Kara Young, Heather Alicia Simms, Leslie Odom, Jr., Vanessa Bell Calloway, Billy Eugene Jones, and Noah Robbins in Purlie Victorious. (Marc J. Franklin)</span>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://purlievictorious.com/about/" class="external" target="_blank"><em><strong>Purlie Victorious: A Non-Confederate Romp Through the Cotton Patch</strong></em></a><strong>, Ossie Davis</strong></p>
<p><a href="https://www.pbs.org/video/purlie-victorious-mitjay/" class="external" target="_blank">Ossie Davis&#8217; madcap romp</a> about a Black preacher&#8217;s attempts to regain his inheritance in the Jim Crow South is all farce logic and linguistic pyrotechnics. If you likewise relish a belly laugh as much as a founding contradiction, it&#8217;s probably time to get your Reed on.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="238537" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/what-to-read-next-based-on-your-favorite-tony-nominee/81njh9gtcql-_ac_uf10001000_ql80_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/81njH9GTCQL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" data-orig-size="638,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="81njH9GTCQL._AC_UF1000,1000_QL80_" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/81njH9GTCQL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-191x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/81njH9GTCQL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" class="size-medium wp-image-238537 aligncenter" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/81njH9GTCQL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-191x300.jpg" alt="" width="191" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/81njH9GTCQL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-191x300.jpg 191w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/81njH9GTCQL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-38x60.jpg 38w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/81njH9GTCQL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-32x50.jpg 32w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/81njH9GTCQL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg 638w" sizes="(max-width: 191px) 100vw, 191px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Ishmael Reed, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/p/books/flight-to-canada-ishmael-reed/8584872?ean=9780684847504" class="external" target="_blank">Flight to Canada</a></em></strong></p>
<p>This wild, verging-on-preposterous send-up of the fugitive slave narrative is as funny as Purlie&#8217;s foils. Start with this one, then get the rest of the canon out of the library. There&#8217;s a clear line from this mad genius/satirist to <a href="https://www.newyorker.com/magazine/2024/03/18/percival-everett-profile" class="external" target="_blank">Percival Everett</a>.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>WHAT TO READ IF YOU LOVED:</strong></p>
<span class="caption"><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="238638" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/what-to-read-next-based-on-your-favorite-tony-nominee/1_hellskitchen_0023rr/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/1_hellskitchen_0023rr.jpg" data-orig-size="970,546" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="1_hellskitchen_0023rr" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Maleah Joi Moon and company of Hell&#8217;s Kitchen. (Joan Marcus)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/1_hellskitchen_0023rr-300x169.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/1_hellskitchen_0023rr.jpg" class="wp-image-238638 size-full" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/1_hellskitchen_0023rr.jpg" alt="" width="970" height="546" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/1_hellskitchen_0023rr.jpg 970w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/1_hellskitchen_0023rr-300x169.jpg 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/1_hellskitchen_0023rr-768x432.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/1_hellskitchen_0023rr-60x34.jpg 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/1_hellskitchen_0023rr-50x28.jpg 50w" sizes="(max-width: 970px) 100vw, 970px" /> Maleah Joi Moon and company of Hell&#8217;s Kitchen. (Joan Marcus)</span>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em><a href="https://www.hellskitchen.com/?utm_source=google&amp;utm_medium=cpc&amp;utm_campaignid=20819397045&amp;utm_adgroupid=154871114623&amp;utm_adid=683411388417&amp;utm_term=hells%20kitchen%20broadway&amp;utm_matchtype=b&amp;utm_campaign=TTG_media_g_NY_acq_search_Hells_Kitchen&amp;utm_adgroup=Media_Hells_Kitchen_All&amp;gad_source=1&amp;gclid=CjwKCAjw1K-zBhBIEiwAWeCOF94Fajz2uGxsZj_T2Asdr334IkthTHLUOPmm4pSTmFH8oADFMqNTHBoCQZkQAvD_BwE" class="external" target="_blank"><strong>Hell&#8217;s Kitchen</strong></a><strong>, </strong></em><strong>Alicia Keys and Kristoffer Diaz</strong></p>
<p>Alicia Keys&#8217; jukebox musical is a sumptuous coming-of-age celebration, concerning a 17 year old New Yorker with artistic dreams.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="238600" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/what-to-read-next-based-on-your-favorite-tony-nominee/attachment/33294200/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/33294200.jpg" data-orig-size="1688,2550" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="33294200" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/33294200-199x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/33294200-678x1024.jpg" class="size-medium wp-image-238600 aligncenter" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/33294200-199x300.jpg" alt="" width="199" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/33294200-199x300.jpg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/33294200-678x1024.jpg 678w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/33294200-768x1160.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/33294200-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/33294200-1017x1536.jpg 1017w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/33294200-1356x2048.jpg 1356w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/33294200-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/33294200.jpg 1688w" sizes="(max-width: 199px) 100vw, 199px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Elizabeth Acevedo, <a href="https://bookshop.org/p/books/the-poet-x-elizabeth-acevedo/6819808?ean=9780062662811" class="external" target="_blank"><em>The Poet X</em></a></strong></p>
<p>That put me in mind of this much lauded young adult novel from Elizabeth Acevedo. This National Book Award nominee is told in verse, and it follows Xiomara, another rising poet living in the big city.</p>
<p>If you (rightly) love the ecstatic prose but prefer the R rating, <a href="https://lithub.com/meet-national-book-award-finalist-elizabeth-acevedo/">Acevedo</a> recently published her first novel for adults. Check out her magically tinged, multi-generational novel, <a href="https://bookshop.org/p/books/family-lore-elizabeth-acevedo/19021718?ean=9780063207264" class="external" target="_blank"><em>Family Lore</em></a>.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>WHAT TO READ IF YOU LOVED:</strong></p>
<span class="caption"><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="238639" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/what-to-read-next-based-on-your-favorite-tony-nominee/illinoise_broadway_0681_pjzedit_v001/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/ILLINOISE_BROADWAY_0681_PJZEDIT_v001.jpg" data-orig-size="970,546" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="ILLINOISE_BROADWAY_0681_PJZEDIT_v001" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Ben Cook and company of Illinoise. (Matthew Murphy)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/ILLINOISE_BROADWAY_0681_PJZEDIT_v001-300x169.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/ILLINOISE_BROADWAY_0681_PJZEDIT_v001.jpg" class="wp-image-238639 size-full" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/ILLINOISE_BROADWAY_0681_PJZEDIT_v001.jpg" alt="" width="970" height="546" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/ILLINOISE_BROADWAY_0681_PJZEDIT_v001.jpg 970w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/ILLINOISE_BROADWAY_0681_PJZEDIT_v001-300x169.jpg 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/ILLINOISE_BROADWAY_0681_PJZEDIT_v001-768x432.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/ILLINOISE_BROADWAY_0681_PJZEDIT_v001-60x34.jpg 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/ILLINOISE_BROADWAY_0681_PJZEDIT_v001-50x28.jpg 50w" sizes="(max-width: 970px) 100vw, 970px" /> Ben Cook and company of Illinoise. (Matthew Murphy)</span>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em><strong><a href="https://illinoiseonstage.com/?gad_source=1&amp;gclid=CjwKCAjw1K-zBhBIEiwAWeCOF1lZObYsP7Put_QRk2tFj2oSyrRPg95KLtBP_eqzfU6_pDc8Vkjh8BoCU5cQAvD_BwE" class="external" target="_blank">Illinoise</a>, </strong></em><strong>Sufjan Stevens, Jackie Sibblies Drury, and Justin Peck</strong></p>
<p>This movement theatre piece scored by Sufjan Stevens&#8217; opus-of-the-aughts is effectively an Odyssey. (Boy leaves home, trouble befalls him, boy fights<b>—</b>or dances<b>—</b>his way back home.) Its cipher-y hero also put me in mind of <a href="https://lithub.com/redefining-the-modern-flaneuse-a-reading-list/">the flaneur</a>, who wanders the world of a book in search of spiritual transformation.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="238619" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/what-to-read-next-based-on-your-favorite-tony-nominee/91qkk5sdufl-_ac_uf10001000_ql80_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/91qKK5sdUFL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" data-orig-size="667,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="91qKK5sdUFL._AC_UF1000,1000_QL80_" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/91qKK5sdUFL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-200x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/91qKK5sdUFL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" class="size-medium wp-image-238619 aligncenter" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/91qKK5sdUFL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-200x300.jpg" alt="" width="200" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/91qKK5sdUFL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-200x300.jpg 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/91qKK5sdUFL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/91qKK5sdUFL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/91qKK5sdUFL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg 667w" sizes="(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Olivia Laing, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/p/books/the-lonely-city-adventures-in-the-art-of-being-alone-olivia-laing/8388301?ean=9781250118035" class="external" target="_blank">The Lonely City</a> </em></strong></p>
<p>For another genre-queer meditation on great American cities, and the saving graces of art, look no further than excellent amble.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>WHAT TO READ IF YOU LOVED:</strong></p>
<span class="caption"><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="238640" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/what-to-read-next-based-on-your-favorite-tony-nominee/552_tom-pecinka-and-sarah-pidgeon-in-stereophonic_photo-by-julieta-cervantes/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/552_Tom-Pecinka-and-Sarah-Pidgeon-in-STEREOPHONIC_Photo-by-Julieta-Cervantes.jpg" data-orig-size="970,546" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="552_Tom-Pecinka-and-Sarah-Pidgeon-in-STEREOPHONIC_Photo-by-Julieta-Cervantes" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Tom Pecinka and Sarah Pidgeon in Stereophonic. (Julieta Cervantes)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/552_Tom-Pecinka-and-Sarah-Pidgeon-in-STEREOPHONIC_Photo-by-Julieta-Cervantes-300x169.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/552_Tom-Pecinka-and-Sarah-Pidgeon-in-STEREOPHONIC_Photo-by-Julieta-Cervantes.jpg" class="wp-image-238640 size-full" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/552_Tom-Pecinka-and-Sarah-Pidgeon-in-STEREOPHONIC_Photo-by-Julieta-Cervantes.jpg" alt="" width="970" height="546" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/552_Tom-Pecinka-and-Sarah-Pidgeon-in-STEREOPHONIC_Photo-by-Julieta-Cervantes.jpg 970w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/552_Tom-Pecinka-and-Sarah-Pidgeon-in-STEREOPHONIC_Photo-by-Julieta-Cervantes-300x169.jpg 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/552_Tom-Pecinka-and-Sarah-Pidgeon-in-STEREOPHONIC_Photo-by-Julieta-Cervantes-768x432.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/552_Tom-Pecinka-and-Sarah-Pidgeon-in-STEREOPHONIC_Photo-by-Julieta-Cervantes-60x34.jpg 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/552_Tom-Pecinka-and-Sarah-Pidgeon-in-STEREOPHONIC_Photo-by-Julieta-Cervantes-50x28.jpg 50w" sizes="(max-width: 970px) 100vw, 970px" /> Tom Pecinka and Sarah Pidgeon in Stereophonic. (Julieta Cervantes)</span>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://stereophonicplay.com/?utm_source=gsearch&amp;utm_medium=psearch&amp;utm_keyword=&amp;utm_content=TonyNomGoogleSearchV3&amp;utm_campaign=postopen&amp;gad_source=1&amp;gclid=CjwKCAjw1K-zBhBIEiwAWeCOF6rVAQohy8lZ9j3QiD4e5E2SW7jLX_cJMq8t27JsjAo-Kyg2raVHNBoC4mYQAvD_BwE" class="external" target="_blank"><em><strong>Stereophonic</strong></em></a>, <strong>David Adjmi</strong></p>
<p>Adjmi&#8217;s opus follows a 70s rock band as they struggle through all kinds of interpersonal drama to make a masterpiece. My personal favorite contribution to the whole, rangy canon of rock n&#8217; roll texts is an autobiography from a recurring fly on a similar studio&#8217;s wall.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="238621" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/what-to-read-next-based-on-your-favorite-tony-nominee/71t5vw5q-l-_ac_uf10001000_ql80_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/71t5VW5q-L._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" data-orig-size="689,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="71t5V+W5q-L._AC_UF1000,1000_QL80_" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/71t5VW5q-L._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-207x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/71t5VW5q-L._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" class="size-medium wp-image-238621 aligncenter" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/71t5VW5q-L._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-207x300.jpg" alt="" width="207" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/71t5VW5q-L._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-207x300.jpg 207w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/71t5VW5q-L._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-41x60.jpg 41w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/71t5VW5q-L._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-34x50.jpg 34w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/71t5VW5q-L._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg 689w" sizes="(max-width: 207px) 100vw, 207px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Pamela Des Barres, <a href="https://bookshop.org/p/books/i-m-with-the-band-confessions-of-a-groupie-pamela-des-barres/7400310?ean=9781556525896" class="external" target="_blank"><em>I&#8217;m With the Band: Confessions of a Groupie</em></a></strong></p>
<p>Written by the woman who inspired Penny Lane in <em>Almost Famous, </em>this memoir is, on the one hand, just an outrageous good time. But there&#8217;s tenderness under the sweat. In lush, earnest prose, Des Barres captures what it really feels like to be a fan.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="238598" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/what-to-read-next-based-on-your-favorite-tony-nominee/71y8n5q9uol-_ac_uf10001000_ql80_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/71Y8n5Q9UOL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" data-orig-size="663,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="71Y8n5Q9UOL._AC_UF1000,1000_QL80_" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/71Y8n5Q9UOL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-199x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/71Y8n5Q9UOL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-238598 aligncenter" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/71Y8n5Q9UOL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-199x300.jpg" alt="" width="199" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/71Y8n5Q9UOL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-199x300.jpg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/71Y8n5Q9UOL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/71Y8n5Q9UOL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/71Y8n5Q9UOL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg 663w" sizes="(max-width: 199px) 100vw, 199px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Dawnie Walton, <a href="https://bookshop.org/p/books/the-final-revival-of-opal-nev-dawnie-walton/16520505?ean=9781982140175" class="external" target="_blank"><em>The Final Revival of Opal &amp; Nev </em></a></strong></p>
<p>And on the fiction tip, the rock stars in this historical collage novel are as lovingly imagined as Adjmi&#8217;s unnamed underdogs.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>WHAT TO READ IF YOU LOVED:</strong></p>
<span class="caption"><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="238641" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/what-to-read-next-based-on-your-favorite-tony-nominee/01-the-outsiders-the-greasers-photo-by-matthew-murphy/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/01.-The-Outsiders-The-Greasers-Photo-by-Matthew-Murphy.jpg" data-orig-size="970,546" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="01.-The-Outsiders-The-Greasers-Photo-by-Matthew-Murphy" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Jason Schmidt, Renni Anthony Magee, Daryl Tofa, Tilly Evans-Krueger, Sky Lakota-Lynch, Joshua Boone, Brent Comer, and Brody Grant. (Matthew Murphy)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/01.-The-Outsiders-The-Greasers-Photo-by-Matthew-Murphy-300x169.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/01.-The-Outsiders-The-Greasers-Photo-by-Matthew-Murphy.jpg" class="wp-image-238641 size-full" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/01.-The-Outsiders-The-Greasers-Photo-by-Matthew-Murphy.jpg" alt="" width="970" height="546" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/01.-The-Outsiders-The-Greasers-Photo-by-Matthew-Murphy.jpg 970w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/01.-The-Outsiders-The-Greasers-Photo-by-Matthew-Murphy-300x169.jpg 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/01.-The-Outsiders-The-Greasers-Photo-by-Matthew-Murphy-768x432.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/01.-The-Outsiders-The-Greasers-Photo-by-Matthew-Murphy-60x34.jpg 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/01.-The-Outsiders-The-Greasers-Photo-by-Matthew-Murphy-50x28.jpg 50w" sizes="(max-width: 970px) 100vw, 970px" /> Jason Schmidt, Renni Anthony Magee, Daryl Tofa, Tilly Evans-Krueger, Sky Lakota-Lynch, Joshua Boone, Brent Comer, and Brody Grant. (Matthew Murphy)</span>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em><strong><a href="https://outsidersmusical.com/?utm_source=performance-max&amp;utm_medium=native&amp;utm_campaign=operating&amp;gad_source=1&amp;gclid=CjwKCAjw1K-zBhBIEiwAWeCOF_vzyvNjZ8oWj19_ocgARIo7H8dBskK8CwZIHY48YMPUeCLlW8maBhoC49wQAvD_BwE&amp;gclsrc=aw.ds" class="external" target="_blank">The Outsiders</a>, </strong></em><strong>Jonathan Clay, Zach Chance, and the Jamestown Revival</strong></p>
<p>If you love <em>The Outsiders </em>musical, you might love, um, S.E. Hinton&#8217;s <a href="https://bookshop.org/p/books/the-outsiders-s-e-hinton/14928969?ean=9780142407332" class="external" target="_blank"><em>The Outsiders</em></a>. But for fear of being on the nose, I&#8217;ll recommend another vibrant <a href="https://lithub.com/the-50-greatest-coming-of-age-novels/">coming-of-age novel</a> instead.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="211801" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/rabih-alameddines-recommends-the-best-short-books-he-read-in-2022/we-the-animals-4/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/we-the-animals.png" data-orig-size="372,560" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="we the animals" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/we-the-animals-199x300.png" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/we-the-animals.png" class="size-medium wp-image-211801 aligncenter" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/we-the-animals-199x300.png" alt="" width="199" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/we-the-animals-199x300.png 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/we-the-animals-40x60.png 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/we-the-animals-33x50.png 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/we-the-animals.png 372w" sizes="(max-width: 199px) 100vw, 199px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Justin Torres, <a href="https://bookshop.org/p/books/we-the-animals-justin-torres/8247117?ean=9780547844190" class="external" target="_blank"><em>We The Animals</em></a></strong></p>
<p>We&#8217;ve <a href="https://lithub.com/the-50-greatest-coming-of-age-novels/">lauded this one before on the site</a>, so suffice it to say: please go get this book, if you haven&#8217;t already. It&#8217;s a truly luminous look at childhood with a &#8220;poetic soul.&#8221;</p>
<p>If you dig that, you might also enjoy Tommy Orange&#8217;s juggernaut debut, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/p/books/there-there-tommy-orange/12066826?ean=9780525436140" class="external" target="_blank">There,</a></em><a href="https://bookshop.org/p/books/there-there-tommy-orange/12066826?ean=9780525436140" class="external" target="_blank"><em> There</em>.</a> For its sweeping epic-ness, and the humane attention paid to young boys in class conflict.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>WHAT TO READ IF YOU LOVED:</strong></p>
<span class="caption"><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="238642" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/what-to-read-next-based-on-your-favorite-tony-nominee/2-shaina-taub-as-alice-paul/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/2-Shaina-Taub-as-Alice-Paul.jpg" data-orig-size="970,546" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="2-Shaina-Taub-as-Alice-Paul" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Shaina Taub in Suffs. (Joan Marcus)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/2-Shaina-Taub-as-Alice-Paul-300x169.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/2-Shaina-Taub-as-Alice-Paul.jpg" class="wp-image-238642 size-full" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/2-Shaina-Taub-as-Alice-Paul.jpg" alt="" width="970" height="546" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/2-Shaina-Taub-as-Alice-Paul.jpg 970w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/2-Shaina-Taub-as-Alice-Paul-300x169.jpg 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/2-Shaina-Taub-as-Alice-Paul-768x432.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/2-Shaina-Taub-as-Alice-Paul-60x34.jpg 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/2-Shaina-Taub-as-Alice-Paul-50x28.jpg 50w" sizes="(max-width: 970px) 100vw, 970px" /> Shaina Taub in Suffs. (Joan Marcus)</span>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em><strong><a href="https://suffsmusical.com/" class="external" target="_blank">Suffs</a>, </strong></em><strong>Shaina Taub </strong></p>
<p>This eager new musical about the long road to passing the 19th amendment sparkles with history lessons. Alice Paul, Mary Church Terrell, and Ida B. Wells-Barnett are all starring cast-members.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="238605" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/what-to-read-next-based-on-your-favorite-tony-nominee/attachment/9781541600256/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/9781541600256.jpg" data-orig-size="267,400" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="9781541600256" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/9781541600256-200x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/9781541600256.jpg" class="size-medium wp-image-238605 aligncenter" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/9781541600256-200x300.jpg" alt="" width="200" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/9781541600256-200x300.jpg 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/9781541600256-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/9781541600256-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/9781541600256.jpg 267w" sizes="(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong><a href="https://bookshop.org/p/books/vanguard-how-black-women-broke-barriers-won-the-vote-and-insisted-on-equality-for-all-martha-s-jones/14022547?ean=9781541600256" class="external" target="_blank"><em>Vanguard</em></a>, Martha S. Jones</strong></p>
<p>If the beautiful songs leave you hungry for a deeper dive, consider this sharp, elegantly structured account of Black women in the suffrage movement.</p>
<p>And for more inspiring tales of femme organizing in the face of oppression, pick up Saidiya Hartman&#8217;s beautifully woven history, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/p/books/wayward-lives-beautiful-experiments-intimate-histories-of-riotous-black-girls-troublesome-women-and-queer-radicals-saidiya-hartman/8777979?ean=9780393357622" class="external" target="_blank">Wayward Lives, Beautiful Experiments</a>.</em></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>WHAT TO READ IF YOU LOVED:</strong></p>
<span class="caption"><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="238643" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/what-to-read-next-based-on-your-favorite-tony-nominee/6-the-cast-of-water-for-elephants-photo-by-matthew-murphy/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/6-The-cast-of-WATER-FOR-ELEPHANTS-Photo-by-Matthew-Murphy.jpg" data-orig-size="970,546" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="6-The-cast-of-WATER-FOR-ELEPHANTS-Photo-by-Matthew-Murphy" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;The cast of Water for Elephants. (Matthew Murphy)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/6-The-cast-of-WATER-FOR-ELEPHANTS-Photo-by-Matthew-Murphy-300x169.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/6-The-cast-of-WATER-FOR-ELEPHANTS-Photo-by-Matthew-Murphy.jpg" class="wp-image-238643 size-full" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/6-The-cast-of-WATER-FOR-ELEPHANTS-Photo-by-Matthew-Murphy.jpg" alt="" width="970" height="546" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/6-The-cast-of-WATER-FOR-ELEPHANTS-Photo-by-Matthew-Murphy.jpg 970w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/6-The-cast-of-WATER-FOR-ELEPHANTS-Photo-by-Matthew-Murphy-300x169.jpg 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/6-The-cast-of-WATER-FOR-ELEPHANTS-Photo-by-Matthew-Murphy-768x432.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/6-The-cast-of-WATER-FOR-ELEPHANTS-Photo-by-Matthew-Murphy-60x34.jpg 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/6-The-cast-of-WATER-FOR-ELEPHANTS-Photo-by-Matthew-Murphy-50x28.jpg 50w" sizes="(max-width: 970px) 100vw, 970px" /> The cast of Water for Elephants. (Matthew Murphy)</span>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em><strong><a href="https://www.waterforelephantsthemusical.com/?utm_source=google&amp;utm_medium=paid%20search&amp;utm_campaign=water%20for%20elephants&amp;gad_source=1&amp;gclid=CjwKCAjw1K-zBhBIEiwAWeCOF2tsPTZ1qvgB_fgXXFxiK5B_zREnkMsSjtLLv3fVQGUP8sEKdofNbRoCxJ0QAvD_BwE" class="external" target="_blank">Water for Elephants</a>, </strong></em><strong>PigPen Theatre Company and Rick Elice</strong></p>
<p>Here&#8217;s another case with obvious inspo, given that the <em>Water for Elephants</em> musical is adapted from <a href="https://bookshop.org/p/books/water-for-elephants-sara-gruen/16622968?ean=9781565125605" class="external" target="_blank">Sara Gruen&#8217;s best-selling novel</a>. But if you&#8217;ve already inhaled that book, you might consider some other show-biz tales.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="238591" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/what-to-read-next-based-on-your-favorite-tony-nominee/61eszjmuql-_ac_uf10001000_ql80_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/61ESzjMUQL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" data-orig-size="642,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="61ESzjM+UQL._AC_UF1000,1000_QL80_" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/61ESzjMUQL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-193x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/61ESzjMUQL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" class="size-medium wp-image-238591 aligncenter" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/61ESzjMUQL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-193x300.jpg" alt="" width="193" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/61ESzjMUQL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-193x300.jpg 193w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/61ESzjMUQL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/61ESzjMUQL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-32x50.jpg 32w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/61ESzjMUQL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg 642w" sizes="(max-width: 193px) 100vw, 193px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Angela Carter, <a href="https://bookshop.org/p/books/wise-children-angela-carter/10396868?ean=9780374530945" class="external" target="_blank"><em>Wise Children</em></a></strong></p>
<p>This fizzy vaudeville saga following two sister-performers is a bright, bracing, totally singular contribution to the family circus narrative.</p>
<p>On the slightly more unsettling end of the spectrum, there&#8217;s a classic circus novel<b>—</b>Katherine Dunn&#8217;s <a href="https://bookshop.org/p/books/geek-love-katherine-dunn/8517251?ean=9780375713347" class="external" target="_blank"><em>Geek</em> <em>Love</em></a>. And for rangier, character-driven fare, look to László Krasznahorkai&#8217;s <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/p/books/the-melancholy-of-resistance-laszlo-krasznahorkai/7547118?ean=9780811215046" class="external" target="_blank">The Melancholy of Resistance</a>.<br />
</em></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>WHAT TO READ IF YOU LOVED:</strong></p>
<span class="caption"><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="238644" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/what-to-read-next-based-on-your-favorite-tony-nominee/7-cabaret-gayle-rankin-top-as-sally-bowles-and-eddie-redmayne-center-below-as-the-emcee-and-the-kit-kat-girls-in-cabaret-at-the-kit-kat-club-at-the-august-wilson-theatre-photo-by-marc-brenner/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/7-CABARET-Gayle-Rankin-top-as-Sally-Bowles-and-Eddie-Redmayne-center-below-as-the-Emcee-and-the-Kit-Kat-Girls-in-CABARET-at-the-Kit-Kat-Club-at-the-August-Wilson-Theatre.-Photo-by-Marc-Brenner.jpg" data-orig-size="970,546" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="7-CABARET-Gayle-Rankin-top-as-Sally-Bowles-and-Eddie-Redmayne-center-below-as-the-Emcee-and-the-Kit-Kat-Girls-in-CABARET-at-the-Kit-Kat-Club-at-the-August-Wilson-Theatre.-Photo-by-Marc-Brenner" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Gayle Rankin, Eddie Redmayne, and company of Cabaret. (Marc Brenner)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/7-CABARET-Gayle-Rankin-top-as-Sally-Bowles-and-Eddie-Redmayne-center-below-as-the-Emcee-and-the-Kit-Kat-Girls-in-CABARET-at-the-Kit-Kat-Club-at-the-August-Wilson-Theatre.-Photo-by-Marc-Brenner-300x169.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/7-CABARET-Gayle-Rankin-top-as-Sally-Bowles-and-Eddie-Redmayne-center-below-as-the-Emcee-and-the-Kit-Kat-Girls-in-CABARET-at-the-Kit-Kat-Club-at-the-August-Wilson-Theatre.-Photo-by-Marc-Brenner.jpg" class="wp-image-238644 size-full" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/7-CABARET-Gayle-Rankin-top-as-Sally-Bowles-and-Eddie-Redmayne-center-below-as-the-Emcee-and-the-Kit-Kat-Girls-in-CABARET-at-the-Kit-Kat-Club-at-the-August-Wilson-Theatre.-Photo-by-Marc-Brenner.jpg" alt="" width="970" height="546" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/7-CABARET-Gayle-Rankin-top-as-Sally-Bowles-and-Eddie-Redmayne-center-below-as-the-Emcee-and-the-Kit-Kat-Girls-in-CABARET-at-the-Kit-Kat-Club-at-the-August-Wilson-Theatre.-Photo-by-Marc-Brenner.jpg 970w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/7-CABARET-Gayle-Rankin-top-as-Sally-Bowles-and-Eddie-Redmayne-center-below-as-the-Emcee-and-the-Kit-Kat-Girls-in-CABARET-at-the-Kit-Kat-Club-at-the-August-Wilson-Theatre.-Photo-by-Marc-Brenner-300x169.jpg 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/7-CABARET-Gayle-Rankin-top-as-Sally-Bowles-and-Eddie-Redmayne-center-below-as-the-Emcee-and-the-Kit-Kat-Girls-in-CABARET-at-the-Kit-Kat-Club-at-the-August-Wilson-Theatre.-Photo-by-Marc-Brenner-768x432.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/7-CABARET-Gayle-Rankin-top-as-Sally-Bowles-and-Eddie-Redmayne-center-below-as-the-Emcee-and-the-Kit-Kat-Girls-in-CABARET-at-the-Kit-Kat-Club-at-the-August-Wilson-Theatre.-Photo-by-Marc-Brenner-60x34.jpg 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/7-CABARET-Gayle-Rankin-top-as-Sally-Bowles-and-Eddie-Redmayne-center-below-as-the-Emcee-and-the-Kit-Kat-Girls-in-CABARET-at-the-Kit-Kat-Club-at-the-August-Wilson-Theatre.-Photo-by-Marc-Brenner-50x28.jpg 50w" sizes="(max-width: 970px) 100vw, 970px" /> Gayle Rankin, Eddie Redmayne, and company of Cabaret. (Marc Brenner)</span>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em><strong><a href="https://kitkat.club/cabaret-broadway/?ch=fb&amp;gad_source=1&amp;gclid=CjwKCAjw1K-zBhBIEiwAWeCOF3pe9-bxjDyKbIvF32fbte4iqs0PHBuSoRCPMYFkHvWoEpsfLvEGkxoCnWIQAvD_BwE" class="external" target="_blank">Cabaret at the Kit Kat Club</a>, </strong></em><strong>John Kander, Fred Ebb, and Joe Masteroff</strong></p>
<p><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="238539" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/what-to-read-next-based-on-your-favorite-tony-nominee/61zpkwvhuel-_ac_uf10001000_ql80_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/61ZpkWVHuEL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" data-orig-size="625,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="61ZpkWVHuEL._AC_UF1000,1000_QL80_" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/61ZpkWVHuEL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-188x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/61ZpkWVHuEL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" class="size-medium wp-image-238539 aligncenter" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/61ZpkWVHuEL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-188x300.jpg" alt="" width="188" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/61ZpkWVHuEL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-188x300.jpg 188w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/61ZpkWVHuEL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-38x60.jpg 38w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/61ZpkWVHuEL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-31x50.jpg 31w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/61ZpkWVHuEL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg 625w" sizes="(max-width: 188px) 100vw, 188px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Irmgard Keun, <a href="https://bookshop.org/p/books/the-artificial-silk-girl-irmgard-keun/10554307?ean=9781590514542" class="external" target="_blank"><em>The Artificial Silk Girl</em></a></strong></p>
<p>If you&#8217;re rooting for <em>Cabaret </em>this Sunday, you may not particularly enjoy <em>sit-ting /a-lone in-your-room</em>. But if the club ever fails to sate, I recommend staying in with this shimmery novel. As ominous as it is engaging, this diaristic book sees pre-war Berlin through the eyes of Doris, a good-time girl who has a lot in common with Sally Bowles.</p>
<p>And speaking of the toast of Mayfair? You can find the original Sally in Christopher Isherwood&#8217;s <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/p/books/the-berlin-stories-christopher-isherwood/12410427?ean=9780811218047" class="external" target="_blank">Berlin Stories</a>. </em></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>WHAT TO READ IF YOU LOVED:</strong></p>
<span class="caption"><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="238645" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/what-to-read-next-based-on-your-favorite-tony-nominee/victoria-pedretti-caleb-eberhardt-jeremy-strong-in-an-enemy-of-the-people-photo-by-emilio-madrid/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Victoria-Pedretti-Caleb-Eberhardt-Jeremy-Strong-in-An-Enemy-of-the-People-Photo-by-Emilio-Madrid.jpg" data-orig-size="970,546" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Victoria-Pedretti-Caleb-Eberhardt-Jeremy-Strong-in-An-Enemy-of-the-People-Photo-by-Emilio-Madrid" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Victoria Pedretti, Caleb Eberhardt, and Jeremy Strong in An Enemy of the People. (Emilio Madrid)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Victoria-Pedretti-Caleb-Eberhardt-Jeremy-Strong-in-An-Enemy-of-the-People-Photo-by-Emilio-Madrid-300x169.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Victoria-Pedretti-Caleb-Eberhardt-Jeremy-Strong-in-An-Enemy-of-the-People-Photo-by-Emilio-Madrid.jpg" class="wp-image-238645 size-full" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Victoria-Pedretti-Caleb-Eberhardt-Jeremy-Strong-in-An-Enemy-of-the-People-Photo-by-Emilio-Madrid.jpg" alt="" width="970" height="546" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Victoria-Pedretti-Caleb-Eberhardt-Jeremy-Strong-in-An-Enemy-of-the-People-Photo-by-Emilio-Madrid.jpg 970w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Victoria-Pedretti-Caleb-Eberhardt-Jeremy-Strong-in-An-Enemy-of-the-People-Photo-by-Emilio-Madrid-300x169.jpg 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Victoria-Pedretti-Caleb-Eberhardt-Jeremy-Strong-in-An-Enemy-of-the-People-Photo-by-Emilio-Madrid-768x432.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Victoria-Pedretti-Caleb-Eberhardt-Jeremy-Strong-in-An-Enemy-of-the-People-Photo-by-Emilio-Madrid-60x34.jpg 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Victoria-Pedretti-Caleb-Eberhardt-Jeremy-Strong-in-An-Enemy-of-the-People-Photo-by-Emilio-Madrid-50x28.jpg 50w" sizes="(max-width: 970px) 100vw, 970px" /> Victoria Pedretti, Caleb Eberhardt, and Jeremy Strong in An Enemy of the People. (Emilio Madrid)</span>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em><strong><a href="https://anenemyofthepeopleplay.com/" class="external" target="_blank">An Enemy of the People</a>, </strong></em><strong>Henrik Ibsen</strong></p>
<p>Ibsen&#8217;s play about a small town facing ecological disaster is a true talkie. People argue and rationalize. They wrestle <em>toward</em> action. If this kind of polyphony appeals to you, why not pick up another high-stakes conversation?</p>
<p><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="238590" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/what-to-read-next-based-on-your-favorite-tony-nominee/716zjeqda8l-_ac_uf10001000_ql80_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/716zjeqdA8L._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" data-orig-size="652,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="716zjeqdA8L._AC_UF1000,1000_QL80_" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/716zjeqdA8L._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-196x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/716zjeqdA8L._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" class="size-medium wp-image-238590 aligncenter" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/716zjeqdA8L._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-196x300.jpg" alt="" width="196" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/716zjeqdA8L._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-196x300.jpg 196w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/716zjeqdA8L._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/716zjeqdA8L._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/716zjeqdA8L._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg 652w" sizes="(max-width: 196px) 100vw, 196px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Miriam Toews, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/p/books/women-talking-miriam-toews/18527863?ean=9781635574340" class="external" target="_blank">Women Talking</a> </em></strong></p>
<p>This thrilling, anxious-making novel, told in the minutes of an emergency meeting, portrays a community of Mennonite women debating whether or not to leave their homes after suffering horrific abuse. It&#8217;s taut and sharp, but also readable. And yes, it is the second Toews title on this list.</p>
<p>For a more direct analog to the play&#8217;s environmental themes, look to non-fiction. Amitav Ghosh&#8217;s <a href="https://bookshop.org/p/books/the-great-derangement-climate-change-and-the-unthinkable-amitav-ghosh/8296757?ean=9780226526812" class="external" target="_blank"><em>The Great Derangement</em></a> is a favorite for muscular, philosophical wrestling with what it means to face climate catastrophe.</p>
<p>This <a href="https://www.nypl.org/blog/2023/09/08/compelling-climate-fiction-read-it-becomes-nonfiction" class="external" target="_blank">list of compelling climate fiction</a> is also a great trampoline.</p>
<p>Meet you under the marquee!</p>
<p><em>Images <a href="https://playbill.com/" class="external" target="_blank">via</a></em></p>
