<li id="lithub_daily_widget-9" class="widget widget_lithub_daily_widget"><div class="lithub-daily-header"><a href="/category/lit-hub-daily/"><b>Lithub</b> Daily</a></div><h2 class="widgettitle">June 14, 2024</h2>
<a href="https://lithub.com/lit-hub-daily-june-14-2024/"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-238563 size-thumbnail" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/photo-1707227670333-14c8ae1dd214-150x150.jpeg" alt="vision pro" width="150" height="150" /></a>
<ul>
 	<li><a href="https://nymag.com/intelligencer/article/apple-vision-pro-disabled-users.html" class="external" target="_blank">What the Apple Vision Pro headset means to disabled users</a></li>
 	<li><a href="https://www.newyorker.com/magazine/2024/06/17/what-covid-did-to-fiction" class="external" target="_blank">Katy Waldman considers the literature of the pandemic</a></li>
 	<li><a href="https://www.nybooks.com/online/2024/06/13/acts-of-language-isabella-hammad/" class="external" target="_blank"><span style="font-weight: 400">Why so many writers treat pro-Palestine speech as a threat</span></a></li>
</ul>
